  "teacherScripts": {
    "component": "scriptsCard",
    "data": {
      "moduleStart": {
        "UIName": "moduleStart",
        "description": "this will trigger when module starts",
        "content": {
          "ops": [
            {
              "attributes": {
                "underline": true
              },
              "insert": "Play keys one by one while reviewing all vocab. "
            },
            {
              "insert": "\n\n"
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "italic": true
              },
              "insert": "Let’s play with the piano!  "
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "italic": true,
                "bold": true
              },
              "insert": "Girl, boy, hat, tree, book, donkey, rabbit."
            },
            {
              "insert": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "startButtonClicked": {
        "UIName": "startButtonClicked",
        "description": "this will trigger when module starts",
        "content": {
          "ops": [
            {
              "attributes": {
                "underline": true
              },
              "insert": "Click on Start button to activate the correct/incorrect feedback and prompt the students with the first note/word to play. "
            },
            {
              "insert": "\n\n"
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "underline": true
              },
              "insert": "Enable student’s mouse."
            },
            {
              "insert": "\n\n"
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "italic": true,
                "bold": true
              },
              "insert": "Where is the (hat, tree, girl, tree, hat, hat, hat)? The____ is here! "
            },
            {
              "insert": "\n\n"
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "underline": true
              },
              "insert": "Prompt students to play the highlighted notes one by one."
            },
            {
              "insert": "\n\n"
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "italic": true
              },
              "insert": "Let’s sing a song! "
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "italic": true,
                "bold": true
              },
              "insert": "Hat, tree, girl, tree, hat, hat, hat! "
            },
            {
              "insert": "\n\n"
            },
            {
              "attributes": {
                "underline": true
              },
              "insert": "Play/sing the full tune again at a faster pace to complete the activity."
            },
            {
              "insert": " \n\n\n"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  },

  "teacherTips": {
    "component": "tipsCard",
    "data": {
      "moduleStart": {
        "UIName": "Module Start",
        "description": "This will trigger when activity starts.",
        "content": {
          "ops": [
            {
              "insert": "- As you demonstrate the keys, you may use movements from the songs to help the student remember the words. \n\n\n\n\n\n"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "startButtonClicked": {
        "UIName": "startButtonClicked",
        "description": "this will trigger when activity starts ",
        "content": {
          "ops": [
            {
              "insert": "- To provide feedback to students, use the green and red feedback, and the pictures inside, to see when students correctly or incorrectly click their piano keys. \n- Teacher must remember to enunciate and use visual cues if the student doesn’t recall the vocabulary word. \n- Younger students may have trouble with clicking keys fast enough to hear the tune. When student has had a few tries to click keys/review vocab, teacher can sing/play the tune before moving on to the next module.   \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  },
